    "has_children": false,
    "in_trash": false,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "paragraph": {
      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "Making a coffee on the rocks at the back of the river I meet Kgmotso. She is a newly ordained sangoma. She speak about her journey and how she used to be a “slay queen” in the third dimension. Now in the fifth dimension things are slightly more lovey, but she’s found her calling. Togozani with two claps - hands on top of eachother and kneeling - is the greeting for healers. We speak about Leo’s and how I am on this journey as I am a strong person. ",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "Making a coffee on the rocks at the back of the river I meet Kgmotso. She is a newly ordained sangoma. She speak about her journey and how she used to be a “slay queen” in the third dimension. Now in the fifth dimension things are slightly more lovey, but she’s found her calling. Togozani with two claps - hands on top of eachother and kneeling - is the greeting for healers. We speak about Leo’s and how I am on this journey as I am a strong person. ",
